{
  "texts": [
    "Structural validity refers to the degree to which the instrument scores are an adequate reflection of the dimensionality of the construct to be measured.",
    "COSMIN requires that factor analyses or IRT/ Rasch analyses are used to assess structural validity 71.",
    "Internal consistency.",
    "Internal consistency refers to the degree to which the items are interrelated.",
    "COSMIN requires Cronbach's alpha(s) to be calculated for each unidimensional scale or subscale 71."
  ]
}